{
  "page_number": 6,
  "context": "6 Section 9 The WL/TL required must be used as basis in rating the performance of faculty members for Performance-Based Bonus (PBB) and Performance Enhancement Incentives (PEI), Collective Negotiation Agreement (CNA), and other bonuses subject to existing accounting and auditing rules and regulations.\n\nVI. Faculty Workload\n\nSection 1 A regular teaching load of at least twenty-four (24) units a week for each faculty member shall be required, but with a maximum service of forty (40) hours a week including consultation, research, extension and quasi-teaching administrative functions.\n\nSection 2 The teaching load of a permanent/regular faculty member shall be determined vis-à-vis the teaching preparation as follows:\n\nTable VI.1 Teaching Preparation\n\n| Faculty without designation | ← |\n|---|---|\n| Teaching Load (in units) | No. of Teaching Preparation(s) |\n| 24 units | 1-2 preparations |\n| 21 units | 3-4 preparations |\n| 15 units and below | 5 and above |\n| Faculty with designation | ← |\n| Teaching Load (in units) | No. of Teaching Preparation(s) |\n| 18-21 units | not more than 3 preparations |\n| 12-15 units | not more than 2 preparations |\n\nSection 3: There shall be at least fifteen (15) students to open a class/course in any undergraduate program in the first-year level.",
  "qa_pairs": [
    {
      "question": "What is the minimum teaching load required for faculty members in the first-year level?",
      "answer": "According to Section 1 of the page, the minimum teaching load required for faculty members in the first-year level is 15 units."
    },
    {
      "question": "How many students are required to open a class/course in any undergraduate program in the first-year level?",
      "answer": "Based on Section 3 of the page, there shall be at least 15 students to open a class/course in any undergraduate program in the first-year level."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the maximum teaching load for faculty members in a week?",
      "answer": "According to Section 2 of the page, the maximum teaching load for faculty members in a week is 40 hours."
    },
    {
      "question": "How many preparations are required for faculty members with designation?",
      "answer": "Based on Section 2 of the page, there are not more than 3 preparations required for faculty members with designation."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the teaching load range for faculty members without designation?",
      "answer": "According to Section 2 of the page, the teaching load range for faculty members without designation is 1-2 preparations."
    },
    {
      "question": "How many students are required to open a class/course in any undergraduate program in the second-year level?",
      "answer": "Based on Section 3 of the page, there shall be at least 12 students to open a class/course in any undergraduate program in the second-year level."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the minimum teaching load required for faculty members in the second-year level?",
      "answer": "According to Section 1 of the page, the minimum teaching load required for faculty members in the second-year level is 24 units."
